@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Print";
    Layout = "";
}

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <meta charset="utf-8">
    <meta http-equiv="X-UA-Compatible" content="IE=edge">
    <title>CRUD Interface (Demo)</title>
    <!-- Tell the browser to be responsive to screen width -->
    <meta content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1, maximum-scale=1, user-scalable=no" name="viewport">
    <!-- Bootstrap 3.3.7 -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/js/components/bootstrap/dist/js/bootstrap.min.js">
    <!-- Font Awesome -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/js/components/font-awesome/css/font-awesome.min.css">
    <!-- Ionicons -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/js/components/Ionicons/css/ionicons.min.css">
    <!-- Theme style -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="~/css/AdminLTE.css">
    <!-- HTML5 Shim and Respond.js IE8 support of HTML5 elements and media queries -->
    <!-- WARNING: Respond.js doesn't work if you view the page via file:// -->
    <!--[if lt IE 9]>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/html5shiv/3.7.3/html5shiv.min.js"></script>
    <script src="https://oss.maxcdn.com/respond/1.4.2/respond.min.js"></script>
    <![endif]-->
    <!-- Google Font -->
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css?family=Source+Sans+Pro:300,400,600,700,300italic,400italic,600italic">
</head>
<body onload="window.print();">
    <div class="wrapper">
        <!-- Main content -->
        <section class="invoice">
            <!-- title row -->
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-xs-12">
                    <h2 class="page-header">
                        <i class="fa fa-globe"></i> Liquid Assets Pty(Ltd). Sample-Demo-Print
                        <small class="pull-right">Date: @DateTime.Now.ToString("yyyy/MM/dd")</small>
                    </h2>
                </div>
                <!-- /.col -->
            </div>
            <!-- info row -->
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Assessment Criteria</h2>
                <p>This document outlines a skills assessment for developers. The objective of the assessment is to identify the developer’s knowledge in:</p>
                <ul>
                    <li>Object-Oriented Programming (OOP)</li>
                    <li>Session Management</li>
                    <li>Database Connections</li>
                    <li>Security understanding (Access, restrictions, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Data Sanitization</li>
                    <li>MVC or MVVC implementation (Model, View, Controller)</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Assessment Task</h3>
                <p>The candidate should create a CRUD (Create, Read, Update and Delete) interface with login functionality and access controls for Admin and Staff.</p>

                <h3>Evaluation Criteria</h3>
                <ul>
                    <li>Correct usage of Forms</li>
                    <li>Base Configuration settings</li>
                    <li>Class structure: Neat, organized, documented</li>
                    <li>Design patterns implemented</li>
                    <li>Front-end styling (Bootstrap, etc.)</li>
                    <li>Security implementation</li>
                    <li>Data sanitization</li>
                </ul>

                <h3>Conclusion</h3>
                <p>Based on the assessment, we can evaluate the developer's experience and knowledge, taking into account time and planning.</p>
            </div>
            <div class="container">
                <h2>Assessment Criteria</h2>
                <p>Download the document below to view the full assessment criteria:</p>
                <a href="@Url.Action("DownloadPdf", "Home")" download>Download Assessment Criteria PDF</a>
            </div>

            <!-- /.row -->
        </section>
        <!-- /.content -->
    </div>
    <!-- ./wrapper -->
</body>
</html>


